programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Man's Best Friend - Part 2

programme.title: Highway to Heaven

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The People Next Door

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: I Was a Middle Aged Werewolf

programme.sub-title: I Was a Middle Aged Werewolf

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Playing for Keeps
programme.desc: Jonathan casts a retired comic and his movie-star son in a play about a father and son who never got to know each other.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Amazing Man

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: All the Colors of the Heart

programme.sub-title: All the Colors of the Heart

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Heather Frederick
programme.desc: Heather Frederick isn't really as old as she appears. She's old before her time and it's up to Fiona and her team of experts to transform Heather from loveable granny to hot child in the city, in just 10 days.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Funny Girl
programme.desc: Growing up in a family of men, Beverly became one of the boys. Over the years she has struggled to find her own style, which has left her frustrated and ready for a change.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: New Mom, New Look
programme.desc: Cindy has an unusual family. Recently married to an older man, her stepchildren aren't much younger than she is. Her looks are failing her and Cindy now feels she no longer turns heads. Time to make Cindy look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA
programme.desc: Natasha has struggled to get her fashion jewelry business off the ground and lost sight of her own looks along the way. She worried that her tired looks and wardrobe of sweats were hurting sales in a business focused on fashion.
programme.sub-title: This Diva is Back and On Track

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Mirror, Mirror On The Wall
programme.desc: After losing 150 pounds, Angela has a new body, but she can't look in the mirror without noticing all her negative qualities. Cosmetic dentistry and Lasik surgery create a new look, but Angela is the only one who can fill the gap in her life.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Sizing Down And Looking Up
programme.desc: Allison has battled with her weight her entire life, and although she's lost 70 pounds through hard work and exercise, she still feels incredibly self-conscious about her appearance. Allison avoids certain social situations because of her insecurity.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Donna Fuller "One Year On"
programme.desc: Derby wife and mum Donna Fuller was stuck at home and stuck in a rut. Nicky revisits to see if Donna is still a woman who can pass the poll test and look 34.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Finding the Inner Girly Girl
programme.desc: Melissa Harris has devoted her life to raising her two young girls, but she's afraid she's falling short in her motherly duties. We're going to bring out the femme fatale in Melissa so she can be a super mom and role model.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Back To Glamour
programme.desc: Rebecca gets a sophisticated makeover to bring back some of the glamour from her pre-mom days. Now, her husband can recognize the girl he married, but will she look 10 Years Younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Fashion 911
programme.desc: Between two failed marriages, the loss of her father and caring for her ailing mother, Zoe feels life taking its toll on her appearance. She has found happiness in a new marriage, and she wants to feel confident when they are in public together.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Frizzy to Fine
programme.desc: Zina is a makeup artist by trade – a woman who encourages people to look their best to show off their spirit. However, spending all her time working and taking care of her children, Zina realizes she doesn't live by her own advice.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Emma Singh
programme.desc: Busy mum and part time student Emma Singh has a taste for the bad things in life and it shows big time on her face. Cosmetic surgeon Jan Stanek plans to get Emma to travel more lightly and youthfully by ridding Emma of her excess baggage on day one.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Viv Thomas
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team come to the rescue of 48 year old Viv Thomas.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Looking for Mr. Right
programme.desc: Ellen is looking for Mr. Right, but due to very busy work and school schedules she hasn't had any time to take care of her looks. We're going make Ellen stand out in the dating competition as we try to make her look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Du Plessis comes to meet Caroline's plane but he doesn't seem happy – he has seen that the mining company have already started building the road which threatens Leopard's Den.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: The family are making arrangements to leave Leopard's Den, all except Du Plessis who is steadfastly refusing to accept that he has lost his home. He won't use his share of the money from the sale of the land to buy somewhere else.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: The family have been squatting at Leopard's Den as they prepare to make their last stand to prevent the bulldozers from destroying their home. Du Plessis and Fatani bring elephants and a giraffe to dissuade the construction crew from moving in.

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: After the devastating loss of Leopard's Den, the family are split across continents. Caroline, Liv and a heavily pregnant Alice are in the UK, while Danny and Du Plessis have remained in South Africa.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny returns to South Africa with Caroline, Liv and Charlotte. They are all excited to be back and are looking forward to seeing their new home, Clearwater Farm.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Danny has been preparing his pitch for an Endangered Species Project. JLW, a pharmaceutical company, are looking to fund an environmental project and the family hope that this grant money will enable them to buy Leopard's Den and Mara.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny and Ed release two cheetah brothers together, a symbol of their new partnership, but not all of the family are happy about this new start. Caroline is still furious at what she sees as Danny's betrayal of Du Plessis.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: The family are still estranged following Caroline's decision to move back to the decrepit Clearwater house with Du Plessis. Rosie is determined to reunite everyone, and plans a civilised dinner as a step towards reconciliation.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 11
programme.desc: The team is responding to a life-threatening emergency. A cyclist in his 60s, Terrence Williams, is unresponsive and critical after an accident 15 minutes flying time from Auckland, near the small settlement of Maramarua.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Mountain bike fanatic, Blake was out riding when he clipped a tree and crashed into a rock. It's a time critical rescue mission. And what the rescue crew doesn't yet know is that Blake is about to take a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: Motorbike rider, Lachlan was testing out his newly designed dirt-bike track when he lost control on a jump. His femur has been badly shattered. The Air Rescue crew is tasked with flying Lachlan to hospital but his medical dramas have only just begun.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 7
programme.desc: Family man Laurie, an offshore oil rigger, is fresh out of jail and claims he's been framed. He's been charged with causing grievous bodily harm after he was involved in a backstreet brawl 12 months ago. Consular officer, Val is on the case.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 8
programme.desc: Aussie expat, Roger arrives at the Embassy after being robbed by a Lady Boy. He says the Lady Boy burst into his hotel room and stole $800 Aussie dollars, along with his drivers licence and international money cards.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 9
programme.desc: Retired construction worker, Ivan, has come to the Embassy with a major financial problem. He purchased a luxury condo in Phuket two years ago, but he still hasn't received the ownership papers from the developer. And it's not looking good.

programme.title: Big Families: Can't Stop, Won't Stop
programme.desc: We meet three families who are either expecting or planning a baby at the same time as seeing their older children, grow up, move out and start their own families.

programme.title: Big Families: Sibling Rivalry
programme.desc: Our first family have 10 children between the ages of a few months and their early teens. With all of the children so close in age, all of the kids are still at a stage where they desperately need their parents love and attention.

programme.title: Big Families: Price and Prejudice
programme.desc: Our first family are determined not to take government handouts. Dad works, mum stays at home and does the odd job and they budget to stay afloat. In their opinion, it was their choice to have 12 children so it's their responsibility to look after them.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 10
programme.desc: Mark came to Bali 18 months ago to setup an I.T. business with his Indonesian wife. But unbeknownst to Mark, his passport contains a fake immigration stamp that was issued by a fake immigration agent.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Fastest Cars in the World
programme.desc: In this episode, we decide what's hot and what's not in the glamorous world of cars. This time we've decided to focus on the fastest cars.
programme.sub-title: The Fastest Cars in the World

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Expensive Production Cars
programme.desc: Real luxury. The kind of cars that you only dream of. On today's Top Ten Show, we're going to expose the most expensive cars in production.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Ten Slowest Cars
programme.desc: Usually, when you talk about cars, it's all about their speed and velocity. But this time we’ve decided to turn the tables and are going to show you the opposite end of the spectrum: the ten most sluggish cars.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Ten Most Fuel-efficient Cars
programme.desc: Fuel prices keep going up. Oil companies are justifying this with high demands and rising oil prices. And the prices will carry-on going up. So on today's show we are showing you ten of the most fuel-efficient cars.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Unusual Cars of Modern Times
programme.desc: Day in day out, R&D departments of car manufacturers ponder over about what constitutes the perfect car. It has to be extraordinary. It has to stand out and it has to be unique.
programme.sub-title: The Most Unusual Cars of Modern Times

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Successful Cars in the 24h Race
programme.desc: The 24-hour-race at the German Nürburgring is one of the most famous and dangerous long-distance races in the world and in today's program we'll show you the cars that have won the most titles each year.
programme.sub-title: The Most Successful Cars in the 24h Race

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Affordable Hybrid Models
programme.desc: In today's show, we are going to show you the most affordable hybrid models. The trail-blazers are definitely the Japanese, who have a whole bunch of cars to offer.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Oldest Car Manufacturers
programme.desc: It’s time to get nostalgic: who do you think is the most important pioneer of the automotive world? We do a little time travel and trace back the trail of the modern car.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Greatest Car Legends
programme.desc: Some cars are not just a means of transport, but influenced entire generations and became legends on their own. That’s why we won’t talk about expensive, fast or successful cars on this episode.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Ugliest Cars
programme.desc: The car-manufacturers' design departments are constantly tinkering around, in a quest to invent the perfect car. And more often than not, very elegantly-shaped cars are the result.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Beautiful Cars
programme.desc: Today we are going for Lux. It has been said that beauty is in the eye of the beholder. So we promise to maintain some objectivity. Desirable cars are what we want, and what we shall get.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Rarest Automobiles
programme.desc: Most manufacturers sell their models in other countries. The production figures, therefore, easily rise into the hundreds of thousands.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Best Sport Versions of Small Cars
programme.desc: Almost every compact car is now available in a sporty version. And funnily enough the little racers usually have more power under the bonnet than you might think.
programme.sub-title: The Best Sport Versions of Small Cars

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 01
programme.desc: An angry bull, a few English people prepared for the weather and a young, talented race driver - tourists will be venturing down to the infamous 'green hell' of the Nürburgring!

programme.desc: A tuned-up Golf 2, a family sedan from Hannover, Germany and a very special Porsche GT2! We will be looking behind the scenes of the gas station by the curve on the race track where sports cars flock!

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Keys to the Kingdom
programme.desc: The relic left by Ma'el is stolen from the mother ship. Zo'or threatens to destroy a major city if it isn't returned. Liam believes the final chapters contain information on synthesizing core energy.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Street Chase

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Trapped by Time

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Hearts and Minds

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Epiphany

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Dark Horizons
programme.desc: Eight Taelons are killed when protectors' implants are re-calibrated with a new imperative to kill instead of protect Taelons. They fear the Jiridians have found a way to control the CVIs. Meanwhile, their core energy continues to deplete.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Point of No Return
programme.desc: When Street solves the 8th dimension of Ma'el's riddle, a beacon leads Liam to a chamber with a healing pool. However, there is only enough in the healing pool to help 6 Taelons. Zo'or will do anything to insure his own life.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: 55-year-old Gold Coast holidaymaker Irina is in real trouble - she's caught in a deadly ocean rip. Like many tourists, Irena was unaware of the risks of not swimming between the beach flags. The Gold Coast rescue helicopter spots her in the nick of time.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A head-on car collision in Tasmania has left tourists Hong and Xeu Wu fighting for their lives. Ambulance crews have managed to stabilize Mr. Wu but Mrs. Wu is in a critical condition and calling out for her husband.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: A Glenbrook farmer has been left seriously injured after one of his Highland cows has taken to him with its horns.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 02

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 03

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 04
programme.desc: Fog, rain and snow means that a visit to the Eifel region is not that pleasant right now. Nevertheless, the hardcore drivers are out of the track and are not letting the weather get in their way.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 05
programme.desc: The Nürburgring. Here you can really let your hair down on a spectacular and difficult race track and learn how to get fit for motor sports. That is why motor fans come here to the Nürburgring throughout the year!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 06
programme.desc: On today's episode, we will be treating you to some very entertaining clips from the Nürburgring. Expect to see the pedal on the metal and rubber burning up the place!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 07
programme.desc: The weather has cleared up a bit on the Nürburgring and we are finally back on the track. As soon as the snow and ice has gone the horsepower junkies return to the ring to tear it up once again.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 08
programme.desc: On today's show we will be showing you the history of a racing legend who has won the 24-hour race four times in a row: Olaf Manthey. Stick around and perhaps you will find out the secret of his success.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 09
programme.desc: Christian Menzel has asked presenter Miriam to participate in some driver safety training! He will be showing you tips and tricks on what to do in emergency situations.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 10
programme.desc: Spring has finally melted away the snow on the track and life on the Nürburgring is starting to flourish once again. It is full of drivers with gasoline in their hearts and cars that roar around the ring.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 11

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 12

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 13
programme.desc: The fourth race of the VLN season is regarded as a dress rehearsal for the 24 hour race. For the top teams and best drivers this is the last opportunity for a real hard test.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 14
programme.desc: Today, we are going to look back at the highlight of last week. The 24 hour race - as always it was exciting. In addition 'Strong Man Run' and a look at the tourist drivers.
